      • getVote

        public int getVote()
        getter for the vote One of (SUCCESS, RUNTIMEEXCEPTION, TIMEOUT, EXCEPTION). These constants are available in {link SCCallOutConstants} class.

      • setVote

        public void setVote(int vote)
        setter for the vote.

        Indicates whether the unit was (SUCCESS, TIMEOUT , RUNTIMEEXCEPTION, EXCEPTION) SUCCESS and EXCEPTION will have to be set explicitly by the CallOut Implementation. RUNTIMEEXCEPTION and TIMEOUT are handled by the framework.

        SUCCESS needs to be set when the callout implementations execution completed successfully EXCEPTION needs to be set when some checked exception occurs while executing the callout implementation RUNTIMEEXCEPTION will be set by the framework when some unchecked exception occurs while executing the callout implementation TIMEOUT will be set by the framework when the execution of the callout implementation exceeds the timeout interval

        vote vote

      • setException
